# Before you integrate with the GOV.UK One Login Signal Exchange platform 

Before you integrate with the GOV.UK One Login Signals exchange platform, you must decide on

* A value to be used as part of the [audience](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7519#section-4.1.3) claim in the SET
* What signals you would like to receive
* Your expected throughput of users attempting to use GOV.UK One Login.  

You must also setup

* An OAuth2 service that supports the [Client Credential Grant][external.oauth-client-credentials-flow]  
* A receiver service that can receive signals sent by the GOV.UK One Login Transmitter.

You should also

* setup a health check using the verification endpoint

You can

* view your configuration

Find out what you need to do to start [developing your integration][ssfOut.integrating-with-signal-exchange-platform]

